fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.config

Interface Config

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ImmutableConfig
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseBlueprintsConfig, BaseConfig, BerkeleyDbConfig, BlueprintsNeo4jConfig, BlueprintsTinkerConfig, HBaseConfig, InMemoryConfig, MapDbConfig, MongoDbConfig

    @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
public interface Config
extends ImmutableConfig
    A configuration that builds the behavior of BackendFactories and StoreFactory.

    All features are all optional: configuration can be created using all or none of them.

    See Also:
    Resource.load(Map), Resource.save(Map)

      • autoSave

        @Nonnull
Config autoSave(@Nonnegative
                          long chunk)
        Adds the autoSave feature, with a defined chunk, in this configuration.

        WARNING: When chunk is zero, the store will be saved at each call.

        Parameters:
        chunk - the number of database operations between each save
        Returns:
        this configuration (for chaining)
        Throws:
        InvalidConfigException - if the chunk is &lt; 0
